---
id: org.dxos.plugin.studio
name: StudioPlugin
version: 0.1.0
---

A studio for **creative artifacts** in `DXOS` Composer. An `Artifact` is a
media-agnostic unit of creative work — a prompt plus the outputs generated (or
uploaded) from it — spanning images, video, and future media. The plugin owns
the cross-cutting ontology and the generic authoring UI; concrete media
(rendering) and providers (generation) plug in via capabilities and surfaces.

## Design tenets

- **One extensible `Artifact` type**, discriminated by an open-string `kind`
  (`'image' | 'video' | …`). No per-medium ECHO types; new media add *behavior*
  (a renderer + optionally a provider), never columns.
- **Two output relationships**: `variants` (interchangeable alternatives of the
  primary output — the user picks a `cover`) vs. `derived` (downstream products
  such as a video transcript/summary or an image caption).
- **Rendering is a Surface, keyed by `contentType`.** Studio ships defaults
  (`image/*` → `<img>`, `video/*` → embeddable player); any plugin overrides via
  a higher-priority (`Position.first`) surface.
- **Generation is kind-specific.** A provider contributes a `GenerationService`
  for a `kind` with its own **`requestSchema`** (Effect Schema) describing that
  medium's request config; studio renders the request form from the schema (a
  generic `Form`) or a provider-supplied custom UI (a Surface).
- **Layout reuses/extends view types**: a masonry gallery is a
  `Collection<Artifact>`; a spatial lightbox is a `Lightbox` (a board layout over
  referenced Artifacts). Layout is a *view*, not a medium.
- **Credentialed access via Connectors**: providers store an `AccessToken`; the
  generate op resolves it via `CredentialsService`, keyed by the provider's
  `source`.

## Extensions

| Term        | URI                          |
| ----------- | ---------------------------- |
| `type`      | `org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0`      |
| `feat`      | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`      |
| `op`        | `org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0`        |
| `component` | `org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0` |
| `test`      | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0`      |

## Types

```mdl
type Artifact
  desc: >
    A creative artifact (typename org.dxos.type.artifact): a prompt plus the
    outputs produced from it. Media-agnostic; `kind` selects rendering + provider.
  fields:
    name?: string
    kind: string                      # open discriminator: 'image' | 'video' | … (no enum)
    instructions: Ref<Instructions>   # the prompt (rich text; @dxos/compute Instructions)
    config?: Record<string, unknown>  # current generation request config (validated vs provider.requestSchema)
    variants: Ref<Variant>[]          # owned alternatives of the primary output
    cover?: Ref<Variant>              # chosen/primary variant (used for thumbnails)
    derived?: Ref<Obj.Unknown>[]      # downstream products (transcript, summary, caption, upscale…)
    meta?: Record<string, unknown>    # extensibility escape hatch (media-specific extras)
  factory:
    # make({ kind }) creates a child Instructions (owns a Text body) parented to the artifact.
    # makeVideo({ url }) creates a kind:'video' artifact with the source as its cover Variant.
```

```mdl
type Variant
  desc: >
    One produced output (typename org.dxos.type.variant; hidden from the navtree,
    owned by its Artifact). Generated variants carry `generation`; uploaded or
    external ones do not.
  fields:
    contentType?: string              # mime — selects the VariantRenderer surface (image/png, video/mp4, …)
    content?: Ref<Obj.Unknown>        # the materialized asset object: File (bytes) / Text / … (generic ⇒ extensible)
    url?: string                      # ephemeral provider / external source URL until materialized into `content`
    generation?: Generation           # provenance (absent ⇒ uploaded/external)
```

```mdl
struct Generation                     # inline (not an ECHO object) — recorded per generated Variant
  fields:
    provider: string
    model?: string
    prompt?: string                   # resolved/magic prompt actually used
    parameters?: Record<string, unknown>   # provider-specific knobs (resolution, style, safety…) — no schema change
    seed?: number
    createdAt?: string
    requestId?: string
```

```mdl
type Lightbox
  desc: >
    A spatial view (typename org.dxos.type.lightbox) over a set of Artifacts laid
    out on a board grid. Layout is a view concern (reuses react-ui-board's
    BoardLayout); the artifacts are referenced, not owned.
  fields:
    name?: string
    items: Ref<Artifact>[]
    layout: BoardLayout               # { size: { width, height }, cells: Record<id, { x, y, width?, height? }> }
```

Reused, unchanged: `File` (`@dxos/types`) for uploaded/materialized bytes;
`Collection` (`@dxos/echo`, `{name?, objects: Ref[]}`) for a masonry gallery of
Artifacts; `Instructions` (`@dxos/compute`) for the prompt; `Text`
(`@dxos/schema`) for `derived` products.

## Capability contracts

```mdl
type GenerationService                # StudioCapabilities.GenerationService (array capability; one per kind/provider)
  desc: >
    A provider of generation for one `kind`. Resolved by the generate op (by
    kind + optional provider id). Its `requestSchema` drives the request form.
    `generate` receives the prompt merged with the artifact's config and returns
    variant descriptors; the provider validates the request against its own schema.
  fields:
    kind: string                      # 'image' | 'video' | …
    id: string                        # provider id, e.g. 'ideogram'
    label: string
    contentType: string               # default output mime (renderer selection)
    source?: string                   # AccessToken.source for the credential
    connectorId?: string              # Connection.connectorId (for the ConnectorAuth surface)
    requestSchema: Schema             # Effect Schema of the kind-specific request config
    defaultRequest?: Record<string, unknown>
    generate: (request: { prompt, count?, …config }, options: { apiKey?: Redacted<string> })
      => Promise<{ variants: VariantData[] }>
  capability:
    # Capability.make<GenerationService>(`${meta.profile.key}.capability.generation-service`)
```

```mdl
surface VariantRenderer               # role org.dxos.plugin.studio.role.variantRenderer, filtered by contentType
  desc: >
    Renders a variant's content. Studio ships defaults (image/* → <img>,
    video/* → embeddable player / <video>); a plugin overrides for a contentType
    via Position.first.
  data: { variant: { contentType?, url?, content?, generation? }, contentType }

surface GenerateForm                  # role org.dxos.plugin.studio.role.generateForm, filtered by kind
  desc: >
    Studio default renders a schema-driven Form (@dxos/react-ui-form) from
    provider.requestSchema; a provider can override with a kind-specific UI via
    Position.first.
  data: { kind, schema, value, onChange }
```

## Operations

```mdl
op generate
  desc: >
    Generate variants for an Artifact. Resolves the GenerationService (by
    artifact.kind + optional provider), resolves the API key from the
    Connector-managed AccessToken via CredentialsService when `source` is set,
    builds the request from the prompt (instructions.text) + artifact.config,
    calls generate(), and appends a Variant per result (recording Generation,
    seeding `cover` with the first).
  input:  { artifact: Ref<Artifact>, provider?: string, count?: number }
  output: { count: number }
  errors: [NoGenerationService, MissingCredential, GenerationError]
  services: [Database.Service, Capability.Service, CredentialsService]
  effects: [echo:write]
```

## Components / surfaces

```mdl
component ArtifactArticle
  desc: >
    Media-agnostic article for an Artifact. Toolbar: variant chooser (tabs) +
    Upload + Connect/Generate. Below: the prompt editor, the kind-specific
    GenerateForm (schema-driven or overridden), and either the selected variant
    (rendered via the VariantRenderer surface for its contentType) or the variant
    gallery.
  props: { role, subject: Artifact, attendableId? }

component GalleryArticle
  desc: >
    A masonry of Artifacts in a Collection (guarded: matches Collections whose
    members are Artifacts). Toolbar creates a new Artifact and multi-select deletes.
  props: { role, subject: Collection }

component LightboxArticle
  desc: A spatial board of Artifacts (react-ui-board); each artifact renders as its cover card. Dragging persists layout.
  props: { role, subject: Lightbox, attendableId? }

component ArtifactCard              # CardContent surface for an Artifact
  desc: Cover-variant thumbnail; lets Artifacts compose into collections/boards laid out by the host.

component ImageVariant / VideoVariant   # default VariantRenderer surfaces (image/*, video/*), overridable
```

## Media kinds

```mdl
feat kind:image
  provider: plugin-ideogram (GenerationService id 'ideogram', source 'ideogram.ai')
  requestSchema: { model?, aspectRatio?, negativePrompt?, styleType?, seed? }
  renderer: ImageVariant (<img>)
  content: generated (ephemeral url) or uploaded (Ref<File>)

feat kind:video
  provider: a video GenerationService (e.g. HeyGen, to live in its own headless
    plugin like plugin-ideogram) — enqueue + poll an async job.
  requestSchema: { avatarId?, voiceId?, … } — provider-specific config held in
    Artifact.config; the prompt is Artifact.instructions.
  renderer: VideoVariant (<video>) plays the produced video URL / uploaded bytes.
  variants: each completed generation is a Variant (most-recent-first ⇒ carousel).
```

> Not to be confused with `plugin-video` (unrelated): that plugin *displays*
> videos (embeds) and fetches YouTube transcriptions. Studio's `kind:'video'` is
> about *generating* video artifacts.

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: Author + generate
  req F-1.1: An Artifact opens in ArtifactArticle showing its prompt + kind-specific request form.
  req F-1.2: Generate runs op:generate against the resolved kind provider and appends Variant(s).
  req F-1.3: The request form is rendered from provider.requestSchema unless a kind GenerateForm surface overrides it.
  req F-1.4: When the provider needs a credential and none is connected, the toolbar shows the ConnectorAuth surface.

feat F-2: Variants + rendering
  req F-2.1: Variants render via the VariantRenderer surface matching their contentType; studio provides image/* and video/* defaults.
  req F-2.2: A plugin may override a contentType renderer via a Position.first surface.
  req F-2.3: Uploaded files are appended as Variants with content=Ref<File> and no generation.

feat F-3: Galleries + lightboxes
  req F-3.1: A Collection of Artifacts renders as a masonry gallery; Create adds a new Artifact; multi-select + Delete removes.
  req F-3.2: A Lightbox renders its Artifacts spatially on a board; dragging persists positions.
  req F-3.3: An Artifact renders as a cover card (CardContent) so it composes into host-laid-out collections/boards.
```

## Acceptance

```mdl
test T-1: Generate appends variants (mock provider)
  given: an Artifact{kind:'image'}; a mock GenerationService for 'image' with a requestSchema
  when: op:generate runs
  then: artifact.variants gains a Variant per result (each with a Generation); cover seeded; output.count matches

test T-2: Renderer resolution by contentType
  given: variants with contentType image/png and video/mp4
  then: each renders via the matching VariantRenderer default; a Position.first override wins

test T-3: Kind-specific request form
  given: a provider requestSchema
  then: the default GenerateForm renders a schema-driven Form; a kind GenerateForm surface overrides it

test T-4: Gallery create/delete + multi-select

test T-5: Video playback
  given: an Artifact{kind:'video'} whose cover Variant url is a YouTube/Vimeo/direct URL
  then: VideoVariant renders an embeddable player; uploaded video bytes play in <video>
```

## Providers

- `plugin-ideogram` (`org.dxos.plugin.ideogram`) — headless; contributes the
  `kind:'image'` `GenerationService` (Ideogram API) + a Connector for
  `ideogram.ai`. Depends on `@dxos/plugin-studio/types`.

## Roadmap (out of scope this milestone)

- **Reconcile `plugin-generator`** (AI video/audio generation) into the Artifact
  ontology: its `Generation{type, prompt, avatarId, voiceId, urls, jobId}` maps
  to `Artifact{kind:'video'|'audio'}` — `prompt` → `instructions`,
  `avatarId`/`voiceId` → `config`, `urls` → `variants`. Extract **HeyGen** into
  its own headless provider plugin (`plugin-heygen`, mirroring `plugin-ideogram`):
  a Connector for `heygen.com` + a `GenerationService{kind:'video'}`. Model the
  async job (enqueue → poll) and the avatar/voice pickers as a provider-supplied
  custom `GenerateForm` surface (`listAvatars`/`listVoices`). Add an `audio/*`
  default `VariantRenderer`. Then delete `plugin-generator`.
  (`plugin-video` — video display + YouTube transcription — is unrelated and stays.)
- **Graduate** `Artifact`/`Variant`/`Generation` to `@dxos/types` (namespace
  re-export; no call-site changes).
- **Materialize** ephemeral generated URLs into `File`s for permanence; persist
  the in-flight provider `jobId` on the Artifact so a long poll survives remount.
- Multi-account credential selection; a `DerivedFrom` relation for heavy
  downstream chains.
```
